The New York Stock Exchange has finished up on Thursday, the figures of the american trade balance testify the resumption of the activity of both US and its partners: the Dow Jones won 0,67% and the Nasdaq 0.33%.
According to the closure final figures, Dow Jones Industrial Average moved forward 68,78 points reaching 10.405,83 points, and Nasdaq, mainly technological, 7,13 points reaching 2.190,06 points.
The enlarged Standard & Poor's 500 index has gained 0,58% (6,40 points) to 1.102,35 points.
There is good news coming from various parts of the economy, Piegza Lindsey, of FTN Financial, reckoned.
But it remains anecdotic, she has tempered, believing that the market focused on "The half full glass".
For Peter Cardillo of Avalon Partners, investors are particularly focused on American trade balance figures, "which show that activity is improving in the fourth quarter."
The US trade deficit declined in October by 7.6% as compared to September, to 32.9 billion dollars.
On the opposite analysts expected a deepening of the deficit.
Both imports and exports have increased.
The big news is the growth in the volume of trade, particularly in exportation of goods, which reflects the growth of the economies of the United States' main trading partners, commented Christopher Cornell, of the research firm Economy.com.
However, the new registrations in the US unemployment have risen against all expectations last week, to reach 474.000 requests.
